metadata.name: Lavender Lilith
metadata.description:
My work is inspired by nature, the female face and fundamentally by spring, the season that creates life. 

The flower I have chosen for this Lilith is lavender, a flower with relaxing properties. 

This Lilith is hand sculpting from white clay, bisque fired and dipped inside in a clear glaze solution then fired a second time.

Physical ceramic art for the first buyer.

Each Lilith is a unique piece, and due to the completely handmade nature of the craft can have slight imperfections; although, this adds to the character and life of the piece.

With Love:
